Deemo is one of my favorite games of all time. The music is incredible, the story is heartwarming and heartbreaking, and the overworld, though somewhat minimal, has a mysterious vibe to it that perfectly suits the game. The only complaint I have is the ESRB rating- it shouldn't be E. An integral theme of Deeno is grief. Also, a couple of songs imply suicide.

I love the track selection for the game, and the art style is very nice. Be warned, however, that most of the content requires extra purchases: out of the 298 currently availabe songs (as of June 2019), 47 are in the free version, an extra 26 require purchasing the game (total of 73), 25 require the Forgotten Hourglass DLC (total of 98), and the rest are behind 38 separate 'Collection' purchases.

Firstly, the books are bought separately to support the artists who made the songs. How else are the artists going to get income? Secondly, just because you upgraded to a new phone, doesn't mean Deemo will support it instantly. The developers need time to tweak the game for it to work on Pixel phones, etc. Dropping a star on the ratings because of impatience is ridiculous. That aside, I've played Deemo for years and have always loved it from the beginning. I fnally have the money to buy/support!

Lovely piano rhythm game involving timing black tap and gold slide. Involves a story of a tall slender mystery figure playing a piano when suddenly a little girl falls from the a window in the sky, causing the figure to rush to catch her. The girl, unsure of where she is, wishes to go home. But as it turns out, the best way to do so in this world is to grow a tree which seems to grow upon hearing new songs. Also if you are into fandoms, the legacy this game has left is overall challenging but a beautiful experience. With much safe for work fan art and discussion
